From 5e9931c72cdbe735fae242b435fe67012035f04f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hari Naraayana Desikan Kannan <hnaraaya@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Sep 2025 21:44:30 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: wifi: cfg80211: Fix link removal
 validation in ML reconfiguration

If there's only one link and a multi-link reconfiguration request
tries to add new links while removing another, the current logic
wrongly rejects it.

Update the validation to check both existing and newly added
links so that valid reconfiguration requests are accepted.

Signed-off-by: Hari Naraayana Desikan Kannan <hnaraaya@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/mac80211/cfg.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/cfg.c b/net/mac80211/cfg.c
index d345f6295c62..40533c19f0eb 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/cfg.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/cfg.c
@@ -6171,7 +6171,7 @@ static int ieee80211_sta_assoc_ml_reconf(struct wiphy *wiphy,
 	if ((added_links & req->rem_links) ||
 	    !(added_links | req->rem_links) ||
 	    ((sta->sta.valid_links & req->rem_links) != req->rem_links) ||
-	    !(sta->sta.valid_links & ~req->rem_links))
+	    !((sta->sta.valid_links | added_links) & ~req->rem_links))
 		return -EINVAL;
 
 	new_active_links = sta->sta.valid_links & ~req->rem_links;
-- 
2.34.1

